               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17910413-40-person490">
                  WILLIAM
                   READ
               <interp inst="t17910413-40-person490" type="surname" value="READ"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17910413-40-person490" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17910413-40-person490" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I went up to the top of the church and found the lead recently cut, by the brightness of the lead; they took some from the top, where the rain would have come in.</p>
               <p>Did you point out that to Mr. Newel? - Yes, we both remarked it; Mr. Newel has forgot it at least. I never saw this man till I saw him before the Justice.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17910413-40-person491">
                  GODFREY
                   HOLDWORTH
               <interp inst="t17910413-40-person491" type="surname" value="HOLDWORTH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17910413-40-person491" type="given" value="GODFREY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17910413-40-person491" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I work for Mr. Porter, and was at work with him, and saw two men working on the church; the prisoner was one, pulling and hauling the lead, as if he wanted to divide it asunder; I saw him also in the public-house.</p>
               <p>Mr. Knowlys. You did not go on the church? - No.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17910413-40-verdict228" type="verdictDescription">
